You two are talking informally to each other.

262
00:15:37,477 --> 00:15:39,641
Why you want to talk informally to me too?

263
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:42,379
Do you know what kind of days these are?

264
00:15:42,414 --> 00:15:45,719
To offer drinks to a woman worker?

265
00:15:45,854 --> 00:15:46,859
Making me not want to see you.

266
00:15:46,994 --> 00:15:48,118
Yoon Kyung!

267
00:15:50,117 --> 00:15:54,105
For you, this... ah.

268
00:15:56,150 --> 00:15:57,693
Ah~

269
00:16:00,961 --> 00:16:03,576
Drink, drink, drink.

270
00:16:05,511 --> 00:16:06,788
Really?

271
00:16:07,284 --> 00:16:08,703
Pretend not to know.

272
00:16:08,738 --> 00:16:10,495
Because only a few people know.

273
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:11,559
Yes.

274
00:16:12,482 --> 00:16:14,554
But I was really surprised.

275
00:16:15,089 --> 00:16:17,681
How can Mr. Park and Ms. Yoon?

276
00:16:18,116 --> 00:16:20,681
It's already been about 10 years.

277
00:16:20,816 --> 00:16:22,103
That long?

278
00:16:22,957 --> 00:16:24,500
Why won't they get married?

279
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:26,945
Because Ms. Yoon's family is strict.

280
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:29,101
They won't allow her to marry a divorcee.

281
00:16:29,736 --> 00:16:32,176
So they can't get married.

282
00:16:32,611 --> 00:16:34,857
So they have been going out
and breaking up for 10 years now.

283
00:16:34,892 --> 00:16:36,238
Ah.

284
00:16:36,573 --> 00:16:38,697
Those years must be horrible.

285
00:16:38,898 --> 00:16:41,486
Now it's more that they are used
to each other than love.

286
00:16:41,677 --> 00:16:43,667
And that is more horrible.

287
00:16:44,842 --> 00:16:46,595
Used to?

288
00:16:47,761 --> 00:16:50,178
There sure are all kinds of love.

289
00:16:50,413 --> 00:16:51,734
Yeah.

290
00:16:54,194 --> 00:16:56,068
We are here.

291
00:16:57,734 --> 00:16:59,407
Do you want go around one more time?

292
00:16:59,739 --> 00:17:00,953
One moment.

293
00:17:02,131 --> 00:17:02,998
Yes father.

294
00:17:03,241 --> 00:17:04,638
Why are you calling at this hour?

295
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:10,067
Oh, of course. It's our annual event, I'll go.

296
00:17:11,315 --> 00:17:13,069
I got the airplane tickets.

297
00:17:15,055 --> 00:17:16,007
I understand.

298
00:17:16,272 --> 00:17:18,792
Yes, go to sleep.

299
00:17:19,764 --> 00:17:21,389
What are you so curious about?

300
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:23,629
His voice is very similar to yours, oppa.

301
00:17:23,905 --> 00:17:24,701
Really?

302
00:17:25,236 --> 00:17:26,931
But what is the big event?

303
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:28,137
Fishing.

304
00:17:28,472 --> 00:17:30,763
Wow. Can't I go too?

305
00:17:30,798 --> 00:17:32,817
I've always wanted to fish.

306
00:17:33,279 --> 00:17:36,744
Uh, let's go together another time.

307
00:17:37,413 --> 00:17:41,296
Because this is a trip I go with my father every year.

308
00:17:41,938 --> 00:17:43,334
Ah~

309
00:17:44,175 --> 00:17:46,455
Next time, I will take you a better place.

310
00:17:46,763 --> 00:17:49,018
I know of a really good fishing spot.

311
00:17:49,153 --> 00:17:50,583
Okay.

312
00:17:56,296 --> 00:17:57,548
You said you wanted go around once more.

313
00:17:57,838 --> 00:18:01,005
No, it's okay we have gone around three times.

314
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:02,365
Now you are awake, right?

315
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,613
Yep.

316
00:18:03,895 --> 00:18:04,983
Then go.

317
00:18:05,218 --> 00:18:06,160
Okay.

318
00:18:06,295 --> 00:18:07,469
Bye.

319
00:18:22,349 --> 00:18:25,291
What time is it that she's still not home?

320
00:18:27,045 --> 00:18:29,570
Did they already start a family or something?

321
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,127
Hey.

322
00:18:48,456 --> 00:18:50,253
What's wrong? Are you sick?

323
00:18:51,084 --> 00:18:52,868
I don't smell alcohol.

324
00:18:53,003 --> 00:18:53,685
Hey?

325
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:54,939
Have you gone crazy?

326
00:18:54,974 --> 00:18:56,798
What's wrong?

327
00:19:00,187 --> 00:19:01,341
Hey, hey...

328
00:19:04,305 --> 00:19:05,217
Hey, hey, what's wrong?

329
00:19:05,252 --> 00:19:05,783
Give me that.

330
00:19:05,918 --> 00:19:06,945
What did something go wrong?

331
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:08,625
You even got a flower bouquet.

332
00:19:09,459 --> 00:19:10,564
Ah! That feels good.

333
00:19:11,779 --> 00:19:14,161
Hey bring mine also. Quickly!

334
00:19:14,196 --> 00:19:15,271
Yours?

335
00:19:32,993 --> 00:19:34,815
They were not of joy,

336
00:19:35,567 --> 00:19:38,746
but tears that came from deep of his stomach,
which he was vomiting.

337
00:19:38,981 --> 00:19:39,724
Why?

338
00:19:39,859 --> 00:19:42,083
I don't know, and that's why I don't feel good.

339
00:19:42,618 --> 00:19:45,719
Crazy guy.  He said let's do it, and why is he crying?

340
00:19:46,254 --> 00:19:48,705
He said thanks for accepting his marriage proposal.

341
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:50,674
He said he loves me so much.

342
00:19:51,009 --> 00:19:53,250
He said he can't go on without me.

343
00:19:54,217 --> 00:19:57,769
He said he was going crazy because
he thought I would say no.

344
00:19:57,804 --> 00:20:00,021
He said all that, but...

345
00:20:03,093 --> 00:20:06,366
I... really...

346
00:20:07,322 --> 00:20:11,085
I know I am being cowardly,

347
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:13,661
gutless...

348
00:20:14,357 --> 00:20:16,258
but I checked many times.

349
00:20:16,293 --> 00:20:17,220
What did you check?

350
00:20:17,355 --> 00:20:18,785
If it was really okay?

351
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,566
If he really wanted to get married?

352
00:20:20,701 --> 00:20:23,002
To tell me truthfully.

353
00:20:23,337 --> 00:20:26,924
What an uncouth couple!

354
00:20:26,959 --> 00:20:28,566
Yeah, we are very unrefined.

355
00:20:29,454 --> 00:20:34,383
After crying and crying, we were kicked out
by the train station manager.

356
00:20:35,018 --> 00:20:39,923
I was embarrassed, and now I feel
kind of clueless, not sure what to do.

357
00:20:40,352 --> 00:20:42,349
In the beginning...

358
00:20:42,684 --> 00:20:47,300
I thought I must have been hard on Jung Joo.

359
00:20:47,577 --> 00:20:53,505
So I was sad and my heart felt bad.

360
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:57,615
Crying for four hours... isn't that unfair?

361
00:20:57,750 --> 00:21:00,200
It's not easy for anyone to do.

362
00:21:00,658 --> 00:21:01,855
But...

363
00:21:02,305 --> 00:21:04,900
Why is it that everything he does is so over the top?

364
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:07,499
Did I scare him too much?

365
00:21:07,671 --> 00:21:11,255
When I saw you walk in all senseless,
I thought you were rejected.

366
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:13,400
It doesn't feel right.

367
00:21:14,005 --> 00:21:16,000
What if he dumps me?

368
00:21:16,006 --> 00:21:18,132
I can't live without him...

369
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:19,637
Hey, hey, quit it.

370
00:21:19,872 --> 00:21:21,678
He must've been sad that you didn't
give him an answer for such a long time,

371
00:21:21,713 --> 00:21:23,086
and probably all of those
feelings exploded yesterday.

372
00:21:23,321 --> 00:21:24,430
That can happen.

373
00:21:24,465 --> 00:21:26,104
Why are you overreacting?

374
00:21:29,101 --> 00:21:31,797
He even bought you all the flowers you like.

375
00:21:32,693 --> 00:21:34,458
Those...

376
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:36,831
I bought them.

377
00:21:37,740 --> 00:21:40,765
I bought them on the way
home because I didn't feel right.

378
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:48,397
Hey, quit that marriage.

379
00:21:49,865 --> 00:21:53,951
What are you lacking that you have to accept a
marriage proposal where you didn't even receive flowers?

380
00:21:53,986 --> 00:21:55,545
Without even a ring?

381
00:21:56,674 --> 00:21:58,574
What are his standards?

382
00:21:58,919 --> 00:22:01,573
He's not a wild boar, is he going 
to just forward everything?

383
00:22:02,168 --> 00:22:03,854
And then why does he cry?

384
00:22:03,858 --> 00:22:04,855
Hey.

385
00:22:04,852 --> 00:22:05,640
You.

386
00:22:05,675 --> 00:22:07,449
You are pretty okay.

387
00:22:09,674 --> 00:22:12,625
Someone may think you are really precious,

388
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:16,876
and will be honored to be selected by you.

389
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:20,569
Who is he who has nothing?

390
00:22:24,071 --> 00:22:25,659
What are you looking at?

391
00:22:26,192 --> 00:22:28,221
You idiot, really...

392
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:30,959
Let's just eat.

393
00:22:33,013 --> 00:22:34,920
What do you keep looking at?

394
00:22:34,955 --> 00:22:36,126
Hey.

395
00:22:36,971 --> 00:22:38,142
By any chance...

396
00:22:38,277 --> 00:22:39,333
What?

397
00:22:40,534 --> 00:22:42,053
Are those glasses... aren't they mine?

398
00:22:42,188 --> 00:22:43,165
Huh?

399
00:22:45,925 --> 00:22:49,293
Oh my. I think we switched glasses.

400
00:22:50,003 --> 00:22:51,975
We must also have the same prescription.

401
00:22:52,491 --> 00:22:54,532
Wow, it looks just like mine.

402
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,618
Design is similar too.

403
00:22:57,589 --> 00:23:00,747
Our taste are similar, so it could happen.

404
00:23:00,982 --> 00:23:01,927
Yeah.

405
00:23:02,062 --> 00:23:03,582
It is 30 years.

406
00:23:04,366 --> 00:23:08,968
As we have been living together
don't you think it is becoming worse?

407
00:23:11,311 --> 00:23:13,566
I need to leave this house soon or something.

408
00:23:13,801 --> 00:23:15,733
I might become addicted.

409
00:23:30,005 --> 00:23:31,712
What addiction?

410
00:23:32,201 --> 00:23:34,083
Relationship Addiction.

411
00:23:34,877 --> 00:23:37,562
Honestly, don't you kind of confuse it?

412
00:23:37,797 --> 00:23:38,666
What?

413
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:39,957
Our relationship.

414
00:23:41,082 --> 00:23:42,145
You too?

415
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:46,363
The line we drew as friends... what can I say...

416
00:23:46,498 --> 00:23:48,304
It's the last line of boundary.

417
00:23:49,032 --> 00:23:52,411
It seems that is broken down right?

418
00:23:52,746 --> 00:23:56,380
Sometimes you get weird feelings too right?

419
00:23:56,515 --> 00:23:58,593
And our conversation crosses over that boundary,

420
00:23:58,828 --> 00:24:01,034
Yes, even though it's not serious.

421
00:24:01,269 --> 00:24:02,811
There is no reason for it to be serious.

422
00:24:02,946 --> 00:24:04,513
If it becomes serious, it would be funny.

423
00:24:04,648 --> 00:24:06,313
You were feeling it also.

424
00:24:06,348 --> 00:24:07,696
You too?

425
00:24:08,243 --> 00:24:10,190
I feel much better.

426
00:24:10,525 --> 00:24:13,642
Since we talked about it, it is nothing.
I was worrying by myself for no reason.

427
00:24:13,777 --> 00:24:17,214
After living together in one space... I guess...

428
00:24:17,349 --> 00:24:21,442
Anyways, when we finish this awkward living situation,
we'll go back to the way things were.

429
00:24:21,789 --> 00:24:22,855
So let's not be sensitive.

430
00:24:22,890 --> 00:24:26,422
But looking at how Jung Joo and
Ji Sun are concerned about the matter,

431
00:24:26,434 --> 00:24:28,136
I don't think it is our overreaction.

432
00:24:28,468 --> 00:24:31,517
Even our spectacles are the same,
and they might be uneasy over that.

433
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:33,934
I guess so.

434
00:24:34,269 --> 00:24:36,037
In your eyes, I appeared as a man too...

435
00:24:36,072 --> 00:24:39,515
We are friends, but being closer than family is...

436
00:24:39,550 --> 00:24:41,107
That is not it, is it?

437
00:24:42,579 --> 00:24:43,538
Huh?

438
00:24:45,371 --> 00:24:46,982
The door is open.

439
00:24:47,841 --> 00:24:49,165
I am here.

440
00:24:49,251 --> 00:24:50,370
Jung Joo.

441
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:54,136
Give me some food, wifey.

442
00:24:54,137 --> 00:24:55,152
What?

443
00:24:55,387 --> 00:24:57,486
I want to call you this sometimes.

444
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,679
You worried a lot, right?

445
00:25:03,153 --> 00:25:04,314
You were sad.

446
00:25:04,449 --> 00:25:06,410
Just look at your face...

447
00:25:06,445 --> 00:25:08,135
Yesterday...

448
00:25:08,983 --> 00:25:12,149
Think of it as me becoming an adult.

449
00:25:13,003 --> 00:25:19,668
Noona, you said if I wanted to get married,
there would be a lot of things I had to give up.

450
00:25:20,779 --> 00:25:24,281
And still would it be okay? If I would not regret it?

451
00:25:24,883 --> 00:25:28,440
After giving it all up, I feel really good.

452
00:25:29,111 --> 00:25:31,706
From now on, you are my everything.

453
00:25:34,717 --> 00:25:35,909
Come here.

454
00:25:36,150 --> 00:25:38,119
I love you.

455
00:25:41,220 --> 00:25:45,140
What a pleasant view so early in the morning.

456
00:26:07,905 --> 00:26:09,281
Oh, yes.

457
00:26:11,150 --> 00:26:14,480
He already said he would give up.

458
00:26:15,655 --> 00:26:19,533
Could you give him just a little more time?

459
00:26:20,477 --> 00:26:23,428
Yes, of course.

460
00:26:25,730 --> 00:26:27,007
I understand.

461
00:26:27,042 --> 00:26:29,486
Yes. Yes.

462
00:26:39,063 --> 00:26:41,871
First off, let's get permission from your mom.

463
00:26:41,906 --> 00:26:43,709
She already knows we are dating.

464
00:26:43,844 --> 00:26:45,084
But still...

465
00:26:45,119 --> 00:26:47,807
Your parents will probably be really shocked also.

466
00:26:48,142 --> 00:26:51,622
I will go and tell my mom and dad by myself.

467
00:26:51,657 --> 00:26:53,842
And then you can go with me.

468
00:26:55,342 --> 00:26:56,823
Don't worry.

469
00:26:57,058 --> 00:26:58,995
I can convince them.

470
00:26:59,130 --> 00:27:01,375
I will make sure you don't get hurt, noona.

471
00:27:03,656 --> 00:27:05,837
You're all grown up and you still call him dad?

472
00:27:06,428 --> 00:27:09,193
Ah, I should fix that also.

473
00:27:09,573 --> 00:27:10,720
Father.

474
00:27:11,259 --> 00:27:12,446
Wife.

475
00:27:12,886 --> 00:27:15,787
Aigoo. Don't you just get the chills?

476
00:27:15,822 --> 00:27:18,966
Yes, let's do that slowly.

477
00:27:19,553 --> 00:27:20,336
Ah~

478
00:27:20,371 --> 00:27:23,364
I must also change if I want to meet your parents.

479
00:27:23,499 --> 00:27:25,126
Do it when I'm not here.

480
00:27:25,161 --> 00:27:27,335
Before I just set everything on fire.

481
00:27:28,226 --> 00:27:29,793
But Jung Joo.

482
00:27:30,815 --> 00:27:33,029
How old are your parents?

483
00:27:33,064 --> 00:27:36,722
They got married when they were 20
and I was in her stomach then.

484
00:27:36,757 --> 00:27:37,869
Huh?

485
00:27:40,203 --> 00:27:43,159
43 minus 30.

486
00:27:45,542 --> 00:27:46,738
FIGHTING!

487
00:27:47,803 --> 00:27:49,451
Do well.

488
00:27:49,721 --> 00:27:51,779
You can calculate right?

489
00:28:03,751 --> 00:28:06,831
Yeah, this is better.

490
00:28:07,464 --> 00:28:09,619
Get married.

491
00:28:23,056 --> 00:28:23,877
Unni.

492
00:28:23,912 --> 00:28:27,201
It's unlike you to take a day off. Why?

493
00:28:28,997 --> 00:28:30,800
You are annoyed?

494
00:28:31,135 --> 00:28:33,202
Now that I took a day off should I also try dating?

495
00:28:34,134 --> 00:28:35,469
Is it really you?

496
00:28:36,522 --> 00:28:40,158
Because finally my life is about to go into its next step.

497
00:28:40,393 --> 00:28:42,119
Something happened, right?

498
00:28:43,498 --> 00:28:45,336
I paid off all my debts!

499
00:28:45,571 --> 00:28:46,351
Really?

500
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:48,573
Congratulations.

501
00:28:51,086 --> 00:28:52,785
Congrats.

502
00:28:54,156 --> 00:28:55,090
That's really good.

503
00:28:55,325 --> 00:28:58,693
The bank debt, the debt I owed myself,

504
00:28:58,728 --> 00:29:01,625
and the blame I had for my family is all gone.

505
00:29:02,593 --> 00:29:06,887
It means from now on I can make a fresh start.

506
00:29:07,727 --> 00:29:09,887
Congratulations.

507
00:29:13,121 --> 00:29:14,570
Have some tea.

508
00:29:14,705 --> 00:29:16,025
Thank you.

509
00:29:17,063 --> 00:29:20,862
Wow, there is a day when a card game
is not on your computer screen?

510
00:29:21,684 --> 00:29:23,396
Just wait and see.

511
00:29:23,651 --> 00:29:25,409
Consumer Complaint Center?

512
00:29:25,544 --> 00:29:26,839
What is it?

513
00:29:27,315 --> 00:29:31,869
After researching, I found out this is a huge lawsuit.

514
00:29:37,185 --> 00:29:41,717
This person leaked out what I used my credit card for.

515
00:29:44,683 --> 00:29:46,766
She is dead.

516
00:29:51,418 --> 00:29:52,559
Where is everyone?

517
00:29:52,794 --> 00:29:55,270
They all went to see Author Shin.

518
00:29:57,999 --> 00:29:59,739
You sure did it well.

519
00:29:59,874 --> 00:30:01,956
It's going to be a hit.

520
00:30:01,991 --> 00:30:03,351
It kills right?

521
00:30:03,686 --> 00:30:05,710
You're getting an incentive, right?

522
00:30:06,934 --> 00:30:08,310
What are you doing?

523
00:30:08,445 --> 00:30:10,532
Getting ready to greet our guest.

524
00:30:10,659 --> 00:30:13,596
Shin Joo Young, you're done writing.

525
00:30:14,518 --> 00:30:16,288
Oh, here.

526
00:30:19,526 --> 00:30:21,494
You decided to get married?

527
00:30:21,529 --> 00:30:22,846
Is it already in the papers?

528
00:30:22,981 --> 00:30:24,826
Did you read the article on the San Mi team?

529
00:30:24,961 --> 00:30:27,442
You know oppa was offered a spot on
the team when he graduated high school,

530
00:30:28,163 --> 00:30:32,059
and will go to that team
automatically when he graduates.

531
00:30:32,194 --> 00:30:33,125
But why?

532
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,455
Did that team fail?

533
00:30:34,525 --> 00:30:35,800
Fail? Why would they fail?

534
00:30:35,904 --> 00:30:37,921
The problem is San Mi is doing too well.

535
00:30:37,985 --> 00:30:41,202
San Mi or Jung Joo are none of your business now.

536
00:30:41,278 --> 00:30:43,779
From now on you should not
personally contact Jung Joo either.

537
00:30:43,814 --> 00:30:44,644
Understand?

538
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:45,834
What is it?

539
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:47,104
I'm so curious.

540
00:30:48,912 --> 00:30:52,149
Many times Jung oppa contacted me first.

541
00:30:52,991 --> 00:30:57,028
Because people around him treated him
like a crazy person for going out with you.

542
00:30:57,263 --> 00:30:59,870
He had no other person to discuss those issues.

543
00:31:00,126 --> 00:31:01,582
You think so, right?

544
00:31:04,381 --> 00:31:07,291
As an editor, I should not interfere with your writing.

545
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:10,380
I waited until now, but I will no longer be patient.

546
00:31:10,776 --> 00:31:12,864
Who are you to play around with adults?

547
00:31:13,260 --> 00:31:14,331
The things you do are too dirty,

548
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:16,876
to be excused because you are a child.

549
00:31:17,111 --> 00:31:19,142
It is creepy to look at you like a fanatic fan.

550
00:31:19,177 --> 00:31:21,449
You are too overboard to label
it as just a love interest you have.

551
00:31:21,861 --> 00:31:24,584
Till when are you going to stalk me and Jung Joo?

552
00:31:24,825 --> 00:31:27,691
Do you really want to be
greatly embarrassed once, huh?

553
00:31:27,869 --> 00:31:29,434
Author Shin.

554
00:31:30,887 --> 00:31:34,236
How did you finish all the rewritings already?

555
00:31:34,271 --> 00:31:35,383
This is the final copy.

556
00:31:35,418 --> 00:31:36,604
I'm no longer going to make any changes.

557
00:31:36,943 --> 00:31:37,904
Oh, of course.

558
00:31:37,939 --> 00:31:39,002
I read it so many times.

559
00:31:39,237 --> 00:31:39,810
It's the best.

560
00:31:39,845 --> 00:31:40,732
The best!

561
00:31:40,967 --> 00:31:42,131
Of course.

562
00:31:43,485 --> 00:31:44,931
Nan Hee, good job also.

563
00:31:45,066 --> 00:31:47,581
Yes, I did do a good job.

564
00:31:47,616 --> 00:31:49,226
Let's go eat.

565
00:31:49,261 --> 00:31:50,737
We can also talk about the advertising.

566
00:31:51,355 --> 00:31:54,295
Does our Author Shin like king crabs?

567
00:31:54,757 --> 00:31:55,853
Yes, I like them.

568
00:31:56,625 --> 00:31:58,936
The baseball player that helped with the book...

569
00:31:59,538 --> 00:32:01,926
Ah, he was your boyfriend, right?

570
00:32:01,961 --> 00:32:04,067
Wow, you are so skilled.

571
00:32:04,102 --> 00:32:05,065
Tell him to come also.

572
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,126
I'm going to pay for everything.

573
00:32:08,124 --> 00:32:09,287
Boss.

574
00:32:11,563 --> 00:32:15,735
Can't we just eat by ourselves?

575
00:32:17,456 --> 00:32:20,197
Jung Joo is busy today.

576
00:32:24,219 --> 00:32:27,508
Oh, our Author Shin likes king crabs like me.

577
00:32:27,543 --> 00:32:30,940
It's really delicious there.

578
00:32:31,534 --> 00:32:34,281
Unni, you were really harsh.

579
00:32:34,548 --> 00:32:36,604
Though she deserved it.

580
00:32:36,974 --> 00:32:38,760
Why is she showing tears?

581
00:32:38,795 --> 00:32:40,130
Making me feel bad.

582
00:32:42,494 --> 00:32:43,496
Let's go.

583
00:32:48,177 --> 00:32:51,036
San Mi traded for another pitcher.

584
00:32:51,171 --> 00:32:53,981
Since they have a lot of money,
they sure are doing all kinds of things.

585
00:32:54,016 --> 00:32:56,209
Why are they so greedy for pitchers?

586
00:32:57,195 --> 00:32:58,912
It's really hard to understand you.

587
00:32:58,947 --> 00:33:01,332
Half the life of a pro player is luck.

588
00:33:01,924 --> 00:33:04,068
If you knew it was going to be like this,

589
00:33:04,103 --> 00:33:05,790
you should have just gone right out of
high school when they called you.

590
00:33:06,705 --> 00:33:08,323
Of course because of you,

591
00:33:08,358 --> 00:33:11,490
I was able to raise some scores... but...

592
00:33:11,525 --> 00:33:12,764
Hey, hey, hey...

593
00:33:12,999 --> 00:33:16,112
Coach, I will mix it deliciously for you.

594
00:33:16,147 --> 00:33:19,589
What do you have to say that you're acting so strange?

595
00:33:24,330 --> 00:33:25,419
It's going to be delicious.

596
00:33:25,739 --> 00:33:27,816
Have you seen the edited script, Nan Hee?

597
00:33:28,051 --> 00:33:29,464
After the author looks at it,

598
00:33:29,499 --> 00:33:30,637
we just have to hand it over to the printing press.

599
00:33:30,672 --> 00:33:31,601
What about advertising?

600
00:33:31,736 --> 00:33:33,261
We are in the middle of planning.

601
00:33:33,596 --> 00:33:34,601
Interview?

602
00:33:35,148 --> 00:33:36,886
Well, you do well.

603
00:33:37,275 --> 00:33:38,756
No pressure right?

604
00:33:39,648 --> 00:33:40,568
It doesn't matter.

605
00:33:40,603 --> 00:33:42,664
It's my book, so I will do it well.

606
00:34:09,952 --> 00:34:11,152
Oh, so full.

607
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:13,129
I ate well, aunt.

608
00:34:13,599 --> 00:34:16,362
You go ahead, I need to go to the restroom first.

609
00:34:16,497 --> 00:34:17,855
Then I will go ahead.

610
00:34:18,048 --> 00:34:18,886
Yes.

611
00:34:19,399 --> 00:34:20,527
Let's go.

612
00:34:23,134 --> 00:34:24,261
Author Shin.

613
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:28,261
Can we talk?

614
00:34:28,743 --> 00:34:30,073
Do you want to go drink tea?

615
00:34:30,568 --> 00:34:31,765
Say it here.

616
00:34:32,757 --> 00:34:33,639
Okay.

617
00:34:39,349 --> 00:34:41,083
What I said was a bit harsh.

618
00:34:41,692 --> 00:34:42,844
I will apologize.

619
00:34:43,185 --> 00:34:44,571
It wasn't because I don't know your heart...

620
00:34:44,606 --> 00:34:45,607
That's okay.

621
00:34:47,819 --> 00:34:48,633
Okay.

622
00:34:51,598 --> 00:34:52,536
That's it right?

623
00:34:54,339 --> 00:34:55,141
Yes.

624
00:34:56,013 --> 00:34:57,146
Joo Young.

625
00:34:59,377 --> 00:35:00,994
Because you also worry for Jung Joo,

626
00:35:01,510 --> 00:35:03,073
I'm going to ask you a favor.

627
00:35:03,930 --> 00:35:04,903
Your book,

628
00:35:05,697 --> 00:35:07,800
I wish Jung Joo wouldn't see it.

629
00:35:09,186 --> 00:35:11,851
There were a lot of things that happened,

630
00:35:12,652 --> 00:35:15,278
but after Jung Joo failed his test,
it was really hard for him.

631
00:35:16,381 --> 00:35:17,600
If he sees your book,

632
00:35:17,635 --> 00:35:19,242
he will probably feel very upset.

633
00:35:19,726 --> 00:35:20,899
You understand right?

634
00:35:23,162 --> 00:35:24,919
His life long dream...

635
00:35:25,154 --> 00:35:27,852
You laid out so well in your book like a fantasy.

636
00:35:30,625 --> 00:35:32,859
Let me just say one thing also.

637
00:35:35,486 --> 00:35:36,808
Ms. Hong.

638
00:35:37,536 --> 00:35:38,816
This marriage,

639
00:35:39,663 --> 00:35:41,899
you will regret with all your heart.

640
00:35:47,737 --> 00:35:50,217
That girl is now out right cursing us.

641
00:35:50,955 --> 00:35:52,156
I'm crazy.

642
00:35:52,391 --> 00:35:55,354
After being attacked by her that much,
I mixed words with her again.

643
00:35:57,471 --> 00:35:58,823
Just fall straight

644
00:36:08,367 --> 00:36:09,869
Become three years younger.

645
00:36:10,477 --> 00:36:11,762
No, two years.

646
00:36:12,439 --> 00:36:14,138
If not at least by one year.

647
00:36:20,167 --> 00:36:21,863
There's been no such precedence.

648
00:36:21,898 --> 00:36:23,261
Do you think this is child's play?

649
00:36:23,396 --> 00:36:24,952
College baseball is also an official league.

650
00:36:26,370 --> 00:36:29,333
But still, you let go of players that are
going out to play internationally.

651
00:36:29,951 --> 00:36:31,586
The season is almost ending,

652
00:36:31,910 --> 00:36:34,009
and I will finish off this season well.

653
00:36:34,374 --> 00:36:35,870
You crazy.

654
00:36:35,905 --> 00:36:38,378
If you go to San Mi without finishing school,
do you think they will welcome you?

655
00:36:38,614 --> 00:36:39,771
I know they won't.

656
00:36:40,511 --> 00:36:41,946
But still, I must go against it,

657
00:36:42,629 --> 00:36:45,333
but before that I need your approval.

658
00:36:45,740 --> 00:36:47,358
What's up with you lately?

659
00:36:49,117 --> 00:36:50,425
Wake up.

660
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:52,397
Can't you tell what's up after reading the article?

661
00:36:52,432 --> 00:36:54,841
The situation is twisted seriously.

662
00:36:55,076 --> 00:36:58,162
The league you want to join is filled with pitchers.

663
00:36:58,397 --> 00:37:01,036
You dumped San Mi to try out for the Major League
and now they're swamped with pitchers.

664
00:37:01,492 --> 00:37:03,152
So many pitchers that it's a problem.
Do you think they still need you?

665
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:04,414
I know.

666
00:37:04,549 --> 00:37:06,455
Do you know what the best thing you can do is?

667
00:37:06,593 --> 00:37:08,350
This year and next year win in the college leagues.

668
00:37:08,401 --> 00:37:11,500
And throw so well that
the scouts can have an eye on you.

669
00:37:11,506 --> 00:37:13,100
Then try to get into one of the spots.

670
00:37:13,131 --> 00:37:14,884
That is the best you can do for right now!

671
00:37:15,119 --> 00:37:18,689
Right now is the most important
time in your baseball career.

672
00:37:21,314 --> 00:37:22,097
You.

673
00:37:22,132 --> 00:37:23,997
Why didn't you go to America?

674
00:37:24,132 --> 00:37:25,680
Looking at the San Mi situation now,

675
00:37:25,700 --> 00:37:27,645
you will probably be an alternate after graduation.

676
00:37:27,679 --> 00:37:29,967
You should have just gambled.

677
00:37:30,891 --> 00:37:32,437
I want to make money.

678
00:37:32,913 --> 00:37:34,322
It's okay if I am an alternate.

679
00:37:34,457 --> 00:37:35,147
If I try hard...

680
00:37:35,182 --> 00:37:37,703
Rubbish, rubbish...
Talking as if it is a game.

681
00:37:37,738 --> 00:37:39,143
Do you not know what kind of life
an alternate player leads?

682
00:37:39,178 --> 00:37:42,184
That is not a system where you can
move up because you work hard.

683
00:37:43,379 --> 00:37:45,104
Exactly why are you doing this?

684
00:37:45,139 --> 00:37:47,217
Is your family situation that hard?

685
00:37:48,380 --> 00:37:49,821
I want to get married.

686
00:37:50,682 --> 00:37:52,096
You little.

687
00:37:55,735 --> 00:37:58,873
Before you get settled just date.

688
00:37:59,408 --> 00:38:01,122
I'm so nervous I can't.

689
00:38:01,257 --> 00:38:02,854
And it's hard to concentrate on baseball.

690
00:38:02,889 --> 00:38:03,783
You are 22!

691
00:38:03,818 --> 00:38:04,608
Why are you in such a hurry?

692
00:38:04,743 --> 00:38:05,836
Unless you have a kid...

693
00:38:07,682 --> 00:38:08,871
Do you have a kid on the way?

694
00:38:11,155 --> 00:38:14,276
Then... the girl is old, right?

695
00:38:15,538 --> 00:38:18,189
We have another crazy guy to go, go.

696
00:38:21,145 --> 00:38:22,188
No.

697
00:38:22,572 --> 00:38:24,411
San Mi will not try to take you immediately,

698
00:38:24,546 --> 00:38:26,042
and I also won't let you go.

699
00:38:26,277 --> 00:38:29,520
If you try to mess up the league system,
only then you'll end up as an idiot.

700
00:38:31,195 --> 00:38:33,816
Today I'm going to close my eyes
and pretend this never happened.

701
00:38:34,051 --> 00:38:35,879
If you get blacklisted, you're out of the baseball game for sure.

702
00:38:36,014 --> 00:38:38,520
You cannot even stay in this sport.

703
00:38:38,907 --> 00:38:40,005
Coach.

704
00:38:40,467 --> 00:38:41,457
Jun Joo.

705
00:38:42,393 --> 00:38:44,820
If an athlete meets the wrong woman,

706
00:38:44,955 --> 00:38:46,492
his life is over.

707
00:38:47,399 --> 00:38:52,436
Every baseball you'll ever throw in your career,
adds to your reputation.

708
00:38:52,958 --> 00:38:54,594
If you loosen up.

709
00:38:54,829 --> 00:38:57,581
It's not stop but E-N-D

710
00:38:57,616 --> 00:38:58,648
The end.

711
00:39:03,114 --> 00:39:04,719
Dinner appointment is okay, right?

712
00:39:05,361 --> 00:39:06,642
Yes, I will.

713
00:39:07,588 --> 00:39:09,423
I will take you to a nice place.

714
00:39:11,438 --> 00:39:13,154
I'm going to go.

715
00:39:13,189 --> 00:39:14,360
Why there?

716
00:39:14,495 --> 00:39:16,583
Sunbae has been moved to 
the marketing department there.

717
00:39:16,718 --> 00:39:18,099
They're having trouble in the
commercial department nowadays.

718
00:39:18,134 --> 00:39:19,373
Oh~

719
00:39:19,408 --> 00:39:20,485
Are you going to get them?

720
00:39:21,164 --> 00:39:22,934
I'm just laying some ground work first.

721
00:39:24,267 --> 00:39:25,397
I'll be back.

722
00:39:43,598 --> 00:39:44,521
Try it.

723
00:39:45,433 --> 00:39:46,887
You made all this?

724
00:39:49,967 --> 00:39:50,877
It's delicious.

725
00:39:51,212 --> 00:39:53,760
I've always wanted to do this once up here.

726
00:39:53,895 --> 00:39:54,504
Why?

727
00:39:54,949 --> 00:39:57,593
Because I came up here a lot when I was an intern.

728
00:39:57,728 --> 00:39:58,957
Every time I was sad.

729
00:40:02,252 --> 00:40:03,623
That's when I found this.

730
00:40:04,749 --> 00:40:06,567
It was hard with the other interns.

731
00:40:06,702 --> 00:40:08,673
And because I couldn't get along with the other interns...

732
00:40:08,708 --> 00:40:10,536
I was embarrassed in front
of the other company workers.

733
00:40:10,571 --> 00:40:12,424
And my work here felt strange.

734
00:40:13,472 --> 00:40:16,512
And so, from then on, I started looking
for the owner of this pin.

735
00:40:17,283 --> 00:40:18,542
What are you going to do when you find the owner?

736
00:40:18,577 --> 00:40:21,372
I was going to find it and return it
and maybe have a meal with the owner.

737
00:40:21,507 --> 00:40:23,253
It's a chance to talk to that person.

738
00:40:23,488 --> 00:40:27,657
And since this person comes here a lot,
seems like this person has a lot of sorrows.

739
00:40:28,551 --> 00:40:32,639
But I was not able to find the couple
cuff links that went with this.

740
00:40:33,815 --> 00:40:34,936
And so...

741
00:40:35,071 --> 00:40:38,215
With this smart head, I started solving this mystery.

742
00:40:38,250 --> 00:40:39,212
Hmm~

743
00:40:39,347 --> 00:40:41,524
Looking at the situation.

744
00:40:41,759 --> 00:40:46,059
Find a picture here that wasn't here three months ago.

745
00:40:48,640 --> 00:40:49,900
I found it.

746
00:40:50,829 --> 00:40:52,741
See, it is yours right?

747
00:40:53,978 --> 00:40:55,486
It is yours, right oppa?

748
00:40:56,021 --> 00:40:57,185
I will return it to you.

749
00:40:57,220 --> 00:40:58,527
Who said this was mine?

750
00:41:00,029 --> 00:41:01,046
No..?

751
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:03,967
What is the picture you see that is different?

752
00:41:04,002 --> 00:41:05,060
The billboard.

753
00:41:05,195 --> 00:41:08,056
Yoon Sung Ah used to be right up there.

754
00:41:08,701 --> 00:41:10,362
Why do you pretend not to know?

755
00:41:10,703 --> 00:41:11,551
No.

756
00:41:13,797 --> 00:41:14,746
Me.

757
00:41:17,682 --> 00:41:19,815
Was that only three months ago?

758
00:41:20,344 --> 00:41:22,470
It seems like three years has passed.

759
00:41:22,795 --> 00:41:24,973
Oppa, you have changed?

760
00:41:26,314 --> 00:41:27,494
How?

761
00:41:28,292 --> 00:41:29,979
You are next to me.

762
00:41:32,225 --> 00:41:33,953
Even though I had a dinner appointment,

763
00:41:34,723 --> 00:41:36,774
I'm eating the food you have packed me.

764
00:41:37,109 --> 00:41:38,629
Even though, I'm going to be late
for a important meeting,

765
00:41:38,664 --> 00:41:39,967
I'm spending time with you.

766
00:41:41,817 --> 00:41:43,208
The things I did in the past,

767
00:41:44,405 --> 00:41:46,612
the things I thought I couldn't do again,

768
00:41:47,530 --> 00:41:48,848
I'm doing it now.

769
00:41:49,083 --> 00:41:50,282
You have a meeting?

770
00:41:50,517 --> 00:41:51,856
Is it a dinner appointment?

771
00:41:53,240 --> 00:41:54,578
I plan on being late.

772
00:41:54,950 --> 00:41:55,985
Go quickly.

773
00:41:57,156 --> 00:41:57,758
Why?

774
00:41:57,793 --> 00:41:59,028
It's wasteful, let's eat and go.

775
00:41:59,163 --> 00:42:01,133
You being like this makes me sad.

776
00:42:01,983 --> 00:42:04,749
If you have an appointment or a meeting,
you should tell me you have them.

777
00:42:04,884 --> 00:42:06,826
I feel like I'm being patronized here.

778
00:42:07,201 --> 00:42:08,895
Until now, you still can't get along with me comfortably?

779
00:42:09,030 --> 00:42:10,500
Hey, look at you.

780
00:42:11,209 --> 00:42:13,465
Because I was moved by your preparations that I...

781
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:17,713
But why am I also feeling thankful to you
for considering my feelings first...

782
00:42:25,179 --> 00:42:29,246
Today, we're like a couple who's just starting to date. Right?

783
00:42:29,281 --> 00:42:31,192
Yes, I can feel it.

784
00:42:31,931 --> 00:42:33,775
As a way to go up a level,

785
00:42:34,018 --> 00:42:35,423
I have a request.

786
00:42:35,458 --> 00:42:36,423
What is it?

787
00:42:37,221 --> 00:42:38,438
When we part,

788
00:42:38,963 --> 00:42:41,344
don't show me your backside.

789
00:42:41,989 --> 00:42:43,860
Also look at my backside.

790
00:42:43,995 --> 00:42:45,757
Go, I will watch.

791
00:42:46,392 --> 00:42:47,432
Today I will pass.

792
00:42:47,467 --> 00:42:48,469
Go quickly.

793
00:42:49,371 --> 00:42:50,253
Okay.

794
00:42:51,951 --> 00:42:52,866
Bye.

795
00:43:36,448 --> 00:43:37,668
<i>Congratulations!</i>

796
00:43:37,803 --> 00:43:39,728
You are finally getting married!

797
00:43:39,763 --> 00:43:41,614
We still have a long way to go.

798
00:43:42,538 --> 00:43:43,311
Oppa.

799
00:43:43,903 --> 00:43:45,570
I wonder if my clothes will fit.

800
00:43:45,605 --> 00:43:48,223
Right, because he has such an athletic body...

801
00:43:48,610 --> 00:43:50,161
I meant length.

